OL,7,FEthan and Elizabeth had
OL,8,F"instantaneously and undeservedly"
OL,9,Flost their lives, Mr John said, adding
OL,10,Fthat it was horrific that one of the
OL,11,Fsiblings may have witnessed the other
OL,12,Fbeing "put to death in a beastly
OL,13,Fmanner".
OL,15,FIn a trial of the facts, the
OL,16,Fprosecution sets our the case to the
OL,17,Fjury who decide if the defendant
OL,18,Fcommitted the offences - but the
OL,19,Fdefendant is not part of the
OL,20,Fproceedings and verdicts cannot result
OL,21,Fin criminal convictions.
